race.comment: ELLIS BEACH (2) was too good for a maiden field last start over 1400m at Townsville, scoring by 5 lengths. Aidan Holt was in the saddle on that occasion and retains the mount. Capable of making it two on the trot. The well-related LECONFIELD (4) (half to G2 winner Tuscan Queen) was prominent at the corner but turned in a sub-par run last time out over 1400m at this track after a nice win the start prior. Has his share of talent and is hard to beat in this suitable race. RONS FINEST CHOICE (5) settled well back from a wide draw last time then wound up strongly to finish fourth over 1000m at Townsville. Must be included in calculations. KICKAGOAL KENNY (3) can run well fresh.
